Organization of higher education, study forms and teaching methods. Sources of scientific and professional information, their use, introduction of databases. Types of student papers, base of compiling and outlining student papers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give students - an overview of different areas of informatics and its applications, and possible directions of specialization and jobs, - an overview of different learning styles and skills, time management and learning motivation, - experience in creating academic text and public performance in seminar, - experience of analysing learning time management and goal setteing; - basic skills necessary for learning software engeneering or entrepreneurship.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student - has obtained an overview of different areas of informatics or entrepreneurship and is familiar with possible directions of specialization and career paths; - knows his/her opportunities and peculiarities as a student and is able to rely on them when studying at the university; - consciously and expediently plans his/her studies at the university and draws up his/her study plan for the entire study period; - uses general and specialty-specific learning techniques, chooses the learning method corresponding to his/her goals in the context of the subject, becomes aware of working and non-working learning styles for himself/herself and fellow students based on previous experience; - is able to find motivation for learning and analyse the use of time; - is able to formulate a simple academic text and has experience in presenting it ; - participates in group work; - gets acquainted with the work of a research group of the college or company and analyses his/her learning needs and career opportunities as a specialist in the field of software engineering or entrepreneurship.
